<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">PARSONS ENVISIONS A JAZZ REVIVAL <span class="divider">Â |Â </span></span><!-- end .title --> Richard Parsons, a former chairman of Citigroup, who is working to reopen Mintonâs Playhouse in Harlem, <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2013/03/31/nyregion/envisioning-a-rebirth-of-jazz-in-harlem.html?ref=todayspaper&amp;pagewanted=all">told The New York Times</a> about his early memories of jazz. As a teenager growing up in Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn, he took his senior prom date to the Hickory House restaurant in Manhattan to hear the Billy Taylor Trio, an evening he remembers as his âfirst true adolescent experience.â</p>
